        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 17 at 4:30PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 430 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Reynolds, or 9 miles
east of Butler, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, pea sized hail and frequent cloud to
ground lightning.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Roberta, Reynolds, Knoxville, Nakomis, Lee Pope, Horns, Musella, and
Potterville.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
